22/11/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The opposition Movement for Change (PzP) expelled seven members of its Central Committee on Saturday (November 20st) for opposing the policy implemented by leader Nebojsa Medojevic, and organising a media campaign against the leadership's work. Media reported that the seven criticised leaders for joining a coalition with the New Serbian Democracy and the Socialist People's Party ahead of the May local elections. (RTCG, RTRS, Radio Free Europe, Pcnen - 21/11/10)
